  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, you can find beef jerky and biltong at various locations. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Supermarkets and Grocery Stores**:\n   - **Waitrose**: Some branches carry a selection of jerky and biltong.\n   - **Tesco**: Larger stores often have a range of jerky products.\n   - **Sainsbury's**: Check their speciality food sections for jerky and biltong.\n\n2. **Speciality Food Shops**:\n   - **The Biltong Chef**: Located in various spots around London, this is a go-to for authentic South African biltong.\n   - **The Savanna**: Another great spot for South African biltong, located in areas like Ealing and Uxbridge.\n\n3. **Health Food Stores**:\n   - **Holland & Barrett**: They often carry a variety of jerky, including organic and healthier options.\n\n4. **Farmers' Markets and Food Festivals**:\n   - Keep an eye out for local farmers' markets and food festivals where vendors might sell homemade or artisan jerky and biltong.\n\n5. **Online Retailers**:\n   - If you prefer shopping from home, websites like Amazon UK, Ocado, and even direct from brands like The Biltong Chef offer delivery services.\n\nThese are just a few suggestions, but you'll likely find more options depending on your specific location within London. Enjoy your jerky or biltong!",
